From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: nix-on-z <nix-on-z@s390x>
Date: Thu, 01 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix Parquet statistics (min/max) parsing endianness

IntConverter::convertField reads Parquet column statistics (min_value,
max_value) via unalignedLoad without byte-order conversion. Parquet
stores statistics in little-endian, so on big-endian the values are
byte-swapped. This causes the reader to reject valid Parquet files with
"Statistics have min_value > max_value" when filter pushdown is enabled.

FloatConverter::convertField has the same issue: it reads float/double
statistics via memcpy without LE conversion. IEEE 754 floats stored as
LE bytes produce garbage values on BE without byte-swapping.

Fix:
- IntConverter::convertField: wrap unalignedLoad with fromLittleEndian()
  for 2, 4, and 8-byte integer statistics. 1-byte values need no swap.
- FloatConverter::convertField: byteswap the raw bits of the float/double
  via uint32_t/uint64_t intermediary on big-endian.

On little-endian: fromLittleEndian() is a no-op, and the if-constexpr
block for floats compiles away entirely.

Fixes: 02841_parquet_filter_pushdown, 03036_test_parquet_bloom_filter_push_down,
03261_test_merge_parquet_bloom_filter_minmax_stats,
03262_test_parquet_native_reader_int_logical_type, and any other test
that uses Parquet column index or filter pushdown with numeric types.

NOTE: Must apply after patch 0102 (which defines fromLittleEndian in
Decoding.cpp).
---
diff --git a/src/Processors/Formats/Impl/Parquet/Decoding.cpp b/src/Processors/Formats/Impl/Parquet/Decoding.cpp
--- a/src/Processors/Formats/Impl/Parquet/Decoding.cpp
+++ b/src/Processors/Formats/Impl/Parquet/Decoding.cpp
@@ -1424,9 +1424,9 @@
     switch (input_size)
     {
         case 1: val = unalignedLoad<UInt8>(data.data()); break;
-        case 2: val = unalignedLoad<UInt16>(data.data()); break;
-        case 4: val = unalignedLoad<UInt32>(data.data()); break;
-        case 8: val = unalignedLoad<UInt64>(data.data()); break;
+        case 2: val = fromLittleEndian(unalignedLoad<UInt16>(data.data())); break;
+        case 4: val = fromLittleEndian(unalignedLoad<UInt32>(data.data())); break;
+        case 8: val = fromLittleEndian(unalignedLoad<UInt64>(data.data())); break;
         default: chassert(false);
     }

@@ -1486,6 +1486,15 @@

     T x;
     memcpy(&x, data.data(), sizeof(x));
+    /// Parquet statistics are stored in little-endian; convert to native.
+    if constexpr (std::endian::native != std::endian::little)
+    {
+        using U = std::conditional_t<sizeof(T) == 4, uint32_t, uint64_t>;
+        U bits;
+        memcpy(&bits, &x, sizeof(T));
+        bits = std::byteswap(bits);
+        memcpy(&x, &bits, sizeof(T));
+    }

     /// parquet.thrift says:
     /// (*) Because the sorting order is not specified properly for floating
